column5: Spring has sprung, ducks, geese, swans, starlings, blackbirds and finally heard the chirp of a robin sitting in the tree.
I saw 6 robins this morning and a bear turned over a neighbors BBQ last night so your right, it must be spring, even though we've still got plenty of snow but it's starting to go.
Saw my first Robin yesterday. He looked pissed off! HH
The trips are planned.  The gear is ready.
Still waiting for my spring ring neck pleasent to show up has come every year same time for the last 5 years sticks around for a month or so and then I don’t hear him anymore
Always weird hearing the geese honking and flying over the ice hub.

I can say it’s official the ring neck pheasant was beaking off this morning ,spring is on the way he is still hiding and staying low when he pops out I will try to get a picture and I did see a half dozen robins at work the other day let the growing season begin!!!!! cheers peter
